Name: Cash register
Description (no commas allowed): Cash registers are 1x2 slot loot containers that only contain Roubles.

Name: Cash register TAR2-2
Description (no commas allowed): Bigger than the standard Cash register has a 2x2 grid that only spawns Roubles.

Name: Dead Scav
Description (no commas allowed): Corpse of a deceased scav. A 4x4 loot container that spawns Barter Items Food and Drink PM's and medical loot.

Name: Drawer
Description (no commas allowed): Drawers are loot containers that are interacted with when searching filing cabinets. All filing cabinets currently have 4 drawers. Each drawer is a 2x2 grid.

Name: Jacket (114 key)
Description (no commas allowed): A blue jacket that has a chance to spawn Dorm room 114 Key and medkits. Has a separate loot table from other blue jackets.

Name: Jacket (204 key)
Description (no commas allowed): A brown jacket that spawns barter items as well as the Dorm room 204 Key.

Name: Jacket (machinery key)
Description (no commas allowed): A 2x2 slot brown jacket that only spawns the Machinery key. Has a separate loot table from the other brown jackets.

Name: Jacket (marked key)
Description (no commas allowed): A blue jacket that spawns barter items as well as the Marked key. Unlike the Jacket (204 key) it cannot spawn all lubricant items (WD-40 5L Propane Dry Fuel).

Name: Medbag SMU06
Description (no commas allowed): An SMU06 Medical bag that only spawns medical loot.

Name: Medcase
Description (no commas allowed): A plastic medical case that only spawns medical items. Very similar to the Medbag SMU06 but cannot spawn medikits except for the AI-2 medikit.

Name: PC block
Description (no commas allowed): A computer case that can be searched to find PC components.

Name: Safe
Description (no commas allowed): A loot container that only spawns currency and valuable items. The large black safes share the same loot table as the small safes on top of the blue weapon safe spawns such as in Dorm room 204.

Name: Sport bag
Description (no commas allowed): Sport bags are black and red 4x3 bags that spawns all Barter Items PM's and knives.

Name: Plastic suitcase
Description (no commas allowed): A 3x3 grid Plastic suitcase.

Name: Toolbox
Description (no commas allowed): A small toolbox that contains some barter items.

Name: Wooden Toolbox
Description (no commas allowed): A Large toolbox that contains some barter items.

Name: Grenade box
Description (no commas allowed): Grenade boxes are 2x3 loot containers that only spawn grenades.

Name: Wooden ammo box
Description (no commas allowed): Wooden ammo boxes are 3x3 boxes that only contain ammo.

Name: Wooden crate
Description (no commas allowed): Green wooden crate that spawns military loot.

Name: Weapon box (4x4)
Description (no commas allowed): A 4x4 grid TerraGroup Weapon box that spawns weapons and mods. Note that only weapons that actually fit inside spawn.

Name: Weapon box (5x5)
Description (no commas allowed): A 5x5 grid TerraGroup Weapon box that spawns weapons and mods. Note that only weapons that actually fit inside spawn.

Name: Weapon box (5x2)
Description (no commas allowed): A 5x2 grid TerraGroup Weapon box that spawns weapons mods throwables and meds. Note that only weapons that actually fit inside spawn.

Name: Weapon box (6x3)
Description (no commas allowed): A 6x3 grid TerraGroup Weapon box that spawns weapons and mods. Note that only weapons that actually fit inside spawn.

Name: Ground cache
Description (no commas allowed): A 4x4 grid buried and hidden cache.

Name: Buried barrel cache
Description (no commas allowed): A 3x4 grid buried cache.

Name: Common fund stash
Description (no commas allowed): A 5x5 grid stash

Name: Ration supply crate
Description (no commas allowed): A 5x5 ration supply crate

Name: Technical supply crate
Description (no commas allowed): A 5x5 technical supply crate that contains Industrial and Electronic items

Name: Medical supply crate
Description (no commas allowed): A 5x5 medical supply crate
